subSubSection.paragraph:
Locality and horizon: Lignite beds of the Late Eocene (Priabonian) (
Benammi et al. , 2001
) in Muang and Nuea Khlong districts, Krabi Province , southern Thailand .

All the vertebrae are procoelous. Cervical vertebrae (Kr-C-020, 21, and 043) bear a hypapophysis near the anterior end and present elliptical parapophyses in cross-section (
Fig. 9
).

Kr-C-038 represents a left ilium (
Fig. 10
). Its posterior process is well developed and bears a notch on its dorsal margin. The dorsal part has a rough edge. The supra-acetabular crest is protruding. The anterior margin of the bone is not even but is marked by an anterior process.

Kr-C-025 is a left scapula lacking its distal end (
Fig. 10
). The deltoid crest on the posterolateral margin is sharp and thin. The anterior part connecting with the coracoid is massive, whereas it is thin and flat posteriorly.
